WNYU.about: WNYU is NYU's radio station that is completely operated by NYU students. WNYU broadcasts on 89.1 FM weekdays from 4:00PM to 1:00AM, and on the Internet 24 hours a day, 7 days a week.
WNYU.name: WNYU
WNYU.nowPlayingDescription: Newyorkina: Newyorkina is a podcast that is ...
WNYU.nowPlayingDescriptionLong: Newyorkina: Newyorkina is a podcast that is meant to challenge the way that members of the NYU community interpret and receive pieces of entertainment and media. Rockstars Are Weird: Rockstars are infamously very normal people so we will examine their totally normal stories through a comedic lens. Ball Talk: Join Pasha on a balcony in Brooklyn with 20 high flying minutes of Ball Talk! Look forward to waking up by meandering yet informed NBA and WNBA banter accompanied by a keyboard, a sound effect board setup, and a cup of coffee. Don't Care Didn't Ask: Don't Care, Didn't Ask is a semi-humorous informational pop culture podcast where one of the co-hosts educates the other about a topic that the other co-host has an explicit apathy or even contempt for. The Spotlight: The Spotlight is a podcast for the creatives at NYU, a weekly information session explains what and how they can get involved in creative projects or what they can go see and experience.  Food Memos: Food Memos is a podcast about the significance of the food around us through the lens of an NYU student. Take Two: Join us each week on Take Two, where we dive into the hottest trends, viral memes, must-watch films, binge-worthy TV shows, and everything going viral in pop culture and the media for that week. From our unfiltered takes to the internet's wildest opinions, we're here to break it all down with humor, insight, and a touch of chaos. Globtrotting in Pajamas: Globetrotting in Pajamas is a humorous podcast where co-hosts Hana and Caroline explore their difference in cultural upbringing, and how it manifests in their friendship today. What Do You Do Again?: Help a desperate and unemployed sports find a job as she dives into the obscure,behind the scene jobs in sports. You've never heard of but your favorite sports can't operate without  Psych and Sound: Between humor and heart-to-heart talks, Psyche & Sound is a personal exploration of the universal experiences that make music so good at being so relatable. Bringing to the table my own sense of self shaped by music, current and past trends, and the influence of pop culture, we hope to unpack the powerful emotional impact we experience when we hear "that song"—and why it works as self-therapy, developing our emotional intelligence. From Ms. Lauryn Hill ability to intimately connect through her lyrics, to Brazil's 70s psychedelic rock fueling resistance against a violent dictatorship, we'll try to decode what's behind musical masterminds, and dive into why certain singers can draw us in with nothing but their words or beats, exploring how sounds can shape memories and identities. Essentially, this podcast is all about how music transcends time and culture to touch us deeply—and why it works.  Boomer and Zoomer: Boomer and Zoomer is a variety talk show hosted by WNYU News Director Em Ingram and their father Scott Ingram — former college radio personality, and longtime ad salesman in the Bay Area radio biz. Each episode, Scott and Em dive into a topic of interest, recount their life stories, and work through generational disagreements.  Homies talk Harm Reduction: Join Virgile-Minh and friends as they chat about harm reduction, substance use, and community care. This is a podcast for the homies, by the homies — we invite everyone on the spectrum of use to tune in for chill conversations about a crucial topic: keeping each other safe.
